# GitHub API Configuration
# 
# To enable GitHub API integration, create a Personal Access Token (PAT):
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Select scopes: `repo` (for private repos) or `public_repo` (for public repos only)
# 4. Copy the token below
#
# For local development, copy this file to `.env.local` and add your token.
# For CI/CD (GitHub Actions), use `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` or a custom secret.

GITHUB_TOKEN=your_personal_access_token_here
